sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1319014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Constitutive expression of GFP-REACh2 fusion protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part expresses a E0040.K1319002 fusion protein (EGFP-REACh1) behind a J23101 promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Florian Gohr, Arne Zimmermann, Michael Osthege
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part is combined from other BioBricks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We designed this part to be very similar to I20260 and the other fusion parts (K1319013 and K1319015).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Scar25 TAA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence is produced by RFC10-assembly of a RFC25-CDS with a RFC10-prefixed part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Osthege
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is produced by an assembly method.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The resulting sequence is a combination of 9 nucleotides from the RFC25 prefix (acc ggt taa) and the RFC10 scar (tactagag).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: REACh2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RFC[25]-compatible dark quencher based on K1319000 (E0030)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part is a RFC[25] dark quencher that is based upon K1319000 (the RFC[25] version of E0030/EYFP).
Three mutations were introduced that eliminated fluorescence: * L90I * Y145W * H148R
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Osthege, Florian Gohr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part is derived from K1319000.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Point mutations were introduced, starting from K1319000 (RFC25-YFP) as the template.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Scar 25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is the scar produced by assembly using RFC 25.
If you are assembling a composite part using RFC 25, you can insert this part and specify blunt assembly to get the desired sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TEVsite
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
TEV cleaves the following AA sequence with high specificity:
* Glu-Asn-Leu-Tyr-Phe-Gln↓Gly
but:
* Glu-Asn-Leu-Tyr-Phe-Gln↓Ser
is also reported
Note, the part suggested by the Voigt lab, also contains 2 additional 1xGly flanks for increased accessibility.
See also:
* BBa_I712077 (TEV N-term)
* BBa_I712078 (TEV C-term)
* BBa_I712016 (myri+TEV site, Slovenia team igem2007)
* BBa_J64007 (Dan Widmaier, Voigt lab)
References ===========
Dougherty et al. (1989): Molecular genetic analysis of a plant virus polyprotein cleavage site: a model. PMID: 2669323
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Raik Gruenberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
* gene synthesis
* codon optimized for E. coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the sequence of the SpeI/XbaI scar for RBS-CDS junctions in BioBricks standard assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a shorter scar to ensure proper spacing between the RBS and CDS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SX scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: XbaI/SpeI mixed site. Simply used to aid in entry of parts into the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
